        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 10:03PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 1003 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles northeast of Wray to 13 miles south of
Eckley. Movement was south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Wray around 1010 PM MDT.

This includes Highway 385 between mile markers 231 and 256.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
northeastern Colorado. A Severe Thunderstorm Watch also remains in
effect until 300 AM MDT for northwestern Kansas...and southwestern
Nebraska.</instruction>
